{
  "texts": [
    "(This is not necessarily a problem in itself, but it means such systems cannot be deployed without direct oversight, meaning it is questionable whether they fall within the domain of machine ethics.)",
    "Moreover, even if systems like GenEth were capable of autonomously inferring which of a circumscribed number of pro tanto duties apply in particular situations, there are likely other ethically relevant features that cannot be subsumed under one of these duties, or that affect the importance of the duties in particular situations.",
    "To overcome the uncodifiability problem, then, we require a machine learning method that is capable of extracting morally relevant features on the basis of raw input features, rather than relying on pre-determined morally relevant features.",
    "Therefore, what is required is a bottom-up AMA that uses a deep learning method capable of feature extraction.",
    "The most prominent class of deep learning methods consists of artificial neural networks (ANNs)."
  ]
}